b5b42c65402b2df064/funsor/terms.py#L105) and [Align](https://github.com/pyro-ppl/funsor/blob/da322019d355bd43d564a6b5b42c65402b2df064/funsor/terms.py#L388), which were deleted during the v3 refactoring #17. \r\n\r\nThese are convenience funsors so that e.g. we can define\r\n```py\r\n@funsor.of_shape(reals(), reals(), reals())\r\ndef normal(loc, scale, value):\r\n    return -((value - loc) ** 2) / (2 * scale ** 2) - scale.log() -\r\n        math.log(math.sqrt(2 * math.pi))\r\n```\r\nand ensure its inputs are ordered `(loc, scale, value)` rather than `(value, loc, scale)`.\r\n\r\n## Tasks\r\n\r\nFirst PR:\r\n- [x] Implement a simple `Align` to simply re-order its inputs.\r\n- [x] `Align.eager_*()` methods do not need to preserve alignment; they can simply defer to `self.arg.eager_*()`.\r\n- [x] Make `Funsor.align()` call `Align`\r\n- [x] Use `.align()` in `of_funsor`\r\n- [x] Add `Funsor.align()` tests to test_terms.py\r\n\r\nSecond PR:\r\n- [x] Make `Tensor.align()` call `torch.permute()` under the hood\r\n- [x] Add `Tensor.align()` tests to test_torch.py","closed_by":{"login":"jpchen","id":1869641,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4Njk2NDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1869641?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen","html_url":"https://github.com/jpchen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jpchen/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.gi